<https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_F2_FS_DiscoveryFields.ttl> a ftr:Metric, dqv:Metric, dcat:Resource ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_F2_FS_DiscoveryFields.ttl"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_F2_FS_DiscoveryFields.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcat:landingPage "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_F2_FS_DiscoveryFields.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcterms:title "FAIR Metric - F2 - Metadata - Registry metadata fields for resource discovery"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "FM_F2_FS_DiscoveryFields"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "FM_F2_FS_DiscoveryFields"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:description """**What is being measured?**

This metric evaluates whether the database, standard or policy record includes values for the resource name, description, country, at least one subject, and at least one object type. In FAIRsharing, these correspond to general information metadata fields used to support resource discovery. Expected input is the DOI or URL of the record under evaluation.

**Why should we measure it?**

F2 requires that data are described with rich metadata. These metadata fields provide the minimum descriptive information required for users and systems to discover and understand the scope of the resource described by the record. They support the findability of the resource by enabling potential users to identify what it contains, where it is based, and the research domains and resource types it covers."""^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:keyword "FAIR"^^xsd:string ;
    schema:about "Not applicable"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:applicationArea <http://www.fairsharing.org/ontology/subject/SRAO_0000401> ;
    ftr:inDimension <https://w3id.org/fair/principles/terms/F2> ;
    dcat:version "1.0.0"^^xsd:string ;
    
    
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
     
    
    
    
    
    ftr:supportedBy <https://tools.ostrails.eu/champion>; 
    
